reviews.review: Ignore the critics, let go of the OT and just enjoy this amazing conclusion to the Skywalker saga
Loved it. JJ had to squeeze in a lot to fix the way Rain left it and he did a good job. Almost no cringe.

I actually enjoyed the movie. I think it was way better than The Last Jedi. I understood what JJ abrams was trying to do. It is like what if Carrie Fisher was alive? would the story would have changed or be the same? My audience was filled to the max. My audience there was claps, and gasps, but the biggest claps and Woooo was that moment (and i will not say what moment), I know why Rey did what she did at the end hence that Titanic moment. It makes sense to me. But it is sad about that something is gone sort of speak and I will not say. I think questions that we all had got answered. I did cry. So yeah thats it. I would watch it again

I was really sad.  I'm a huge Star Wars fan, but this movie had no character development, no hero's arc, and it made no sense.  There was this feeling of false grandeur, an empire/order full of clowns, an awkward love pentagon, and plenty of weird animated representations of people who've passed.

It was everything that I could hope for. This universe isn't static, but fluid. We cannot hold it to the same standards of the original trilogy. Things evolve, and that is how I am able to accept all that has transpired.
It was okay. The story and the character development was a bit flat because TLJ ignored all of that. If there would have been a better middle movie part three would have worked much better.
This movie is so predictable and so boring it definitely is NOT worth your time or your money. It's just a lazy copy and paste of episode 6 with minor things changed. It is terrible
While it suffers from writing by committee and poor pacing, this is a return to form for the saga and provides a very good ending to the Skywalker story.

78/100 
Much better than Last Jedi, not the best film in the history of the franchise, but not anywhere as bad as the prequels. Decent (or good) way to end another trilogy.
Well, done! Saved the best of the sequels for last. Tied it all together with several surprises and all and all great movie.
